Design Process
Research

We explored existing workflows for creating design systems and discovered that most tools focus on editing existing systems rather than generating new ones.

This revealed an opportunity to simplify the earliest stage of product design.

Defining the Experience

Rather than asking users to manually configure dozens of settings, we centered the experience around one simple action:

Describe your brand.

Everything else happens automatically.

User Flow
Describe the brand
Select optional mood and industry
Generate design system
Preview generated UI
Edit tokens if needed
Validate accessibility
Export design tokens

The experience was intentionally designed to require minimal learning.

Key Features
AI Brand Interpretation

Users describe their product naturally.

Example:

"A calm, professional fintech platform for West African users."

The AI converts this into structured design tokens.

Automated Token Generation

TokenForge creates:

Semantic color palettes
Typography scales
Spacing systems
Border radius values
Shadow systems
Live Preview

Generated tokens are immediately applied to sample interfaces including:

Buttons
Forms
Cards
Navigation

This allows users to evaluate their system before exporting.

Manual Overrides

Every generated token remains editable.

Changes update the preview instantly without refreshing the page.

Accessibility Checker

Accessibility isn't optional.

TokenForge automatically evaluates color combinations against WCAG standards and highlights combinations that fail contrast requirements.

Export Options

Users can export tokens as:

CSS Variables
Tailwind Configuration
JSON

This bridges the gap between design and development.

Remix

Instead of starting over, users can generate multiple AI variations from an existing design system.

Design Decisions
Natural Language First

We intentionally reduced complexity by replacing dozens of configuration inputs with a conversational prompt.

This lowers the learning curve for beginners while increasing speed for experienced designers.

Live Feedback

Seeing generated tokens applied immediately creates confidence and encourages iteration.

Semantic Naming

Instead of generic color values, TokenForge generates meaningful token names that improve scalability across teams.

Accessibility by Default

Rather than expecting users to perform accessibility audits later, TokenForge integrates accessibility into the generation process.

Challenges

One of our biggest challenges was balancing automation with user control.

If the AI generated everything without customization, users might feel restricted.

If users had to configure everything manually, the product would lose its speed advantage.

We solved this through a hybrid workflow where AI creates the initial system while users retain complete editing control.

